d%20civil%20society%20throughout%20the%20world.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20complete%20assault%20on%20press%20freedom%20in%20India%20and%20an%20act%20of%20reprisal%20against%20the%20critical%20and%20independent%20journalism%20of%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Charging%20a%20news%20outlet%20under%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20Prevention%20Act%2C%20is%20a%20brazen%20attempt%20to%20silence%20and%20harass%20independent%20media%2C%20activists%20and%20citizens.%20We%20call%20for%20the%20immediate%20release%20of%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20and%20Amit%20Chakravarty.%20All%20charges%20against%20NewsClick%20must%20be%20dropped%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcountercurrents.org%2F2023%2F10%2Findia-drop-charges-and-release-newsclick-workers-and-end-harassment-of-media%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20David%20Kode%2C%20advocacy%20and%20campaigns%20lead%20at%20CIVICUS.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20raids%20started%20on%20October%203%2C%20with%20the%20police%20seizing%20electronic%20devices%2C%20including%20mobile%20phones%2C%20laptops%20and%20hard%20disks%2C%20of%20journalists.%20So%20far%2C%20the%20police%20have%20questioned%20at%20least%2046%20journalists%20associated%20with%20the%20news%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20journalists%20were%20majorly%20questioned%20on%20matters%20like%20the%202020%20Delhi%20riots%2C%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20movement%20against%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20laws%20and%20the%20COVID-19%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fchronology-samajhiye-5-days-4-agencies-under-modi-govt-control-target-opposition-journalists-activists%5C%22%3EChronology%20Samajhiye%3A%205%20Days%2C%204%20Agencies%20Under%20Modi%20Govt%20Control%20Target%20Opposition%2C%20Journalists%2C%20Activists%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20against%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20apparently%20based%20on%20a%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20that%20says%20the%20portal%20received%20funding%20from%20an%20American%20millionaire%20who%20has%20furthered%20Chinese%20talking%20points.%20The%20%3Cem%3ENYT%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20was%20highlighted%20by%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20MP%20Nishikant%20Dubey%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20who%20claimed%20that%20the%20portal%20and%20Congress%20leaders%20like%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20received%20funds%20from%20China%20to%20create%20an%20%E2%80%9Canti-India%20atmosphere%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20is%20unclear%20what%20charges%20have%20been%20levelled%20against%20the%20individuals%20who%20were%20raided%20or%20questioned.%20The%20search%20notice%20used%20by%20the%20police%20on%20Tuesday%20list%20charges%20under%20various%20sections%20of%20UAPA%2C%20conspiracy%20(section%20120%20B%2C%20IPC)%20and%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20different%20groups%20(153%20A).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20the%20CIVICUS%20Monitor%20has%20documented%20the%20misuse%20of%20the%20UAPA%20law%20by%20Indian%20authorities%20against%20activists%20to%20stifle%20dissent.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22EN%5C%22%20xml%3Alang%3D%5C%22EN%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20crackdown%20against%20independent%20media%20is%20further%20testimony%20of%20the%20deterioration%20of%20civic%20space%20in%20India.%20The%20authorities%20stop%20misusing%20repressive%20laws%20like%20the%20UAPA%20against%20activists%2C%20civil%20society%20and%20journalists.%20They%20must%20comply%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20obligations%20under%20international%20human%20rights%20laws%20and%20standards%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kode%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcountercurrents.org%2F2023%2F10%2Findia-drop-charges-and-release-newsclick-workers-and-end-harassment-of-media%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697356819000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F09132731%2Fnewsclick.jpg%22%2C%2