ing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Football%20Association%20(FA)%20faced%20backlash%20from%20UK%20Culture%20Secretary%20Lucy%20Frazer%20for%20its%20decision%20to%20not%20illuminate%20the%20Wembley%20arch%20in%20the%20colours%20of%20the%20Israeli%20flag%20ahead%20of%20the%20England-Australia%20friendly.%20The%20government%20had%20urged%20sports%20bodies%20to%20appropriately%20acknowledge%20events%20in%20Israel%20and%20Palestine.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20FA%20opted%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmoment%20of%20silence%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cblack%20armbands%E2%80%9D%20for%20players%20to%20honor%20the%20conflict%E2%80%99s%20victims%20during%20the%20match%2C%20instead%20of%20illuminating%20the%20stadium%20in%20Israel%20flag%E2%80%99s%20colours.%20Notably%2C%20representations%20of%20nationalities%20(flags%2C%20bands%2C%20etc.)%20beyond%20England%20and%20Australia%20are%20barred%20from%20Wembley%20Stadium.%20Frazer%20expressed%20%E2%80%9Cdeep%20disappointment%E2%80%9D%2C%20especially%20given%20the%20arch%E2%80%99s%20prior%20illumination%20in%20solidarity%20with%20Ukraine%20after%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion.%20The%20Board%20of%20Deputies%20of%20British%20Jews%20criticised%20the%20FA%20for%20overlooking%20the%20tragic%20loss%20of%20innocent%20lives%20in%20the%20recent%20attacks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697333411000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F14162642%2FF77zdjBWEAENNPg.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Ffootball-israel-palestine-merdeka-cup%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22During%20the%20Qatar%20World%20Cup%20in%202022%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20cause%20drew%20support%20and%20FIFA%20could%20only%20look%20away.%20Now%20again%2C%20with%20passions%20about%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%20raging%20high%2C%20players%20are%20expressing%20their%20views%20and%20clubs%20are%20responding.%20But%20it%20is%20not%20a%20level-playing%20field.%22%2C%22author%